SIMPLE: moleskin
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: moleskin
<hw>mole"skin`</hw> <pr>(m⟦omac⟧l"sk⟦icr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Any fabric having a thick soft shag, like the fur of a
mole; esp., a kind of strong twilled fustian.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A soft fabric having an adhesive backing, applied to
the skin at points susceptible to abrasion, as on the feet, to prevent
irritation or blistering during exercise, such as hiking.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Molest</ent>⟦br⟧
